                <head>395. Editorial Note<note n="1" xml:id="d395fn1">Continued from <ref
                            target="frus1955-57v22#pg_579">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1955–1957, vol. XXII, pp.
                            579</ref> ff.</note>
                </head>
                <p>Substantial additional materials on Southeast Asia are in other volumes of the
                        <ref target="frus1958-60v01">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi> series for the 1958–1960 period.
                        Volume I</ref> is devoted entirely to Vietnam. The East Asia regional
                    compilation, which includes considerable documentation on the Southeast Asia
                    Treaty Organization, is in <ref target="frus1958-60v16">volume XVI</ref>, along
                    with compilations on Cambodia and Laos. A combined microfiche supplement to <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v15">volumes XV</ref> and <ref target="frus1958-60v16"
                        >XVI</ref> has additional materials relating to those three compilations and
                    the entire selection of documents on Burma and Malaya and Singapore.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
